From Mr. Caslin: Here is some information about how you can:
1- Register to Vote or Update your Registration. The deadline to register is October, 5, 2020, if you want to vote for President on November 3, 2020.
2- You MUST apply for an Absentee Ballot, to be able to Vote by Mail. Call - 614-525-3100 if you live in Franklin County, or Call - 877-767-6446 if you live Outside Franklin County.
These are the Early Voting Hours for the Presidential Election of 2020, You can vote early in-person at 1700 Morse Rd, Columbus, Ohio 43229

post_text:
Early College Academy has canceled all in-person classes beginning Monday, March 16, through Friday, April 3, due to the order announced Thursday by Governor Mike DeWine. Early College Academy will remain open on Friday, March 13.
Governor DeWine announced an order on March 12 to close all K-12 school buildings across the state for three weeks, at least through April 3.
Beginning Monday, March 16, all class and school in-person activities are canceled for three weeks through April 3. Coursework will be provided either online or via pick-up between the hours of 9:00 a.m. and 1:00 p.m. You can also call the school at (614) 298-4742 for updates on assignments.
The District is finalizing its distance-learning academic plans and staffing scenarios and will share more information as soon as possible.
Please continue to check the school website at earlycollegecolumbus.com, Facebook (earlycollegecolumbus), and Instagram (ecacolumbus) for updated information.
text:
Early College Academy has canceled all in-person classes beginning Monday, March 16, through Friday, April 3, due to the order announced Thursday by Governor Mike DeWine. Early College Academy will remain open on Friday, March 13.

Beginning Monday, March 16, all class and school in-person activities are canceled for three weeks through April 3. Coursework will be provided either online or via pick-up between the hours of 9:00 a.m. and 1:00 p.m. You can also call the school at (614) 298-4742 for updates on assignments.
The District is finalizing its distance-learning academic plans and staffing scenarios and will share more information as soon as possible.
Please continue to check the school website at earlycollegecolumbus.com, Facebook (earlycollegecolumbus), and Instagram (ecacolumbus) for updated information.

post_text: Isaiah Forte and Martaya Bryant were Youth Experts on a panel at the American Academy of Pediatrics' Annual Meeting this past Friday. This year's conference theme was, "Speak for Those Without a Voice" and "Nothing About Them Without Them"! Isaiah and Martaya, along with four other youth, spoke to a room of over 150 pediatricians and family medicine practitioners about current issues teens face and what doctors can do to help. They spoke on mental health, substance use and abuse, social media, privacy in the doctor's office, improving physician's practice when working with teens, and how to support youth from different backgrounds. We are so proud of the wisdom they shared and how they represented Early College Academy!

They spoke on mental health, substance use and abuse, social media, privacy in the doctor's office, improving physician's practice when working with teens, and how to support youth from different backgrounds. We are so proud of the wisdom they shared and how they represented Early College Academy!
